    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2007-01-04</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2007-01-13T14:43:19Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Homeowner's Tax Relief Act of 2007 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow individual taxpayers an additional tax deduction (whether or not such taxpayers itemize deductions) for state and local real property taxes paid for a principal residence that exceed the national average, as determined by the Secretary of the Treasury. Denies such deduction for taxpayers whose adjusted gross income exceeds $80,000 ($160,000 for joint returns).</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
